## Blockers resolved

### blake3 edition2024 build failure
- `anchor build -p coinflip` failed: blake3 v1.8.3 requires `edition2024` (MSRV 1.85), but Solana platform-tools bundles Cargo 1.84.0
- Fix: `cargo update -p blake3 --precise 1.8.2` — pinned blake3 to the last version supporting Rust 1.84
- Verified coinflip.so rebuilt with `default = ["mock-vrf"]` feature (312128 bytes)

### Frontend winner derivation (client-side)
- After VRF fulfillment, on-chain phase is `Locked` (not `Settled`), so `winner` field is `null`
- Frontend upgraded phase to "complete" but left `winner: null` — both players saw "You Lost"
- Fix: Added `readVrfRandomness()` and `deriveWinnerFromVrf()` in `chain.ts`

### Vite crash from validator ledger
- solana-test-validator snapshot symlinks crash chokidar
- Fix: Added `server.watch.ignored: ["**/.localnet-ledger/**"]` in `vite.config.ts`

### Playwright strict mode violation
- "Back to Lobby" button matches 2 elements
- Fix: Scoped all locators to `sel.sidebar`

### Player profile creation
- `claim_payout` CPI silently skips if profile doesn't exist
- Fix: Added `ensurePlayerProfiles()` in `localnet-setup.ts`, called only from lifecycle test

### Test ordering
- Renamed test files with numeric prefixes for deterministic execution order

